title.narrative: PROTECTION RESPONSE TO COVID-19

description.narrative: Children and adolescents from Old Havana, as well as caregivers and workers in the homes of children without family protection in the country, receive support and have tools for the prevention and attention of violence in contexts of isolation and social distancing., which contributes to Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice (Covid), Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024, more girls, boys and adolescents from prioritized groups and territories benefit from comprehensive, violence-free prevention and protection services and areas.

description.narrative: Mothers, fathers and other caregivers were accompanied from virtual spaces regarding the respectful upbringing of children and adolescents and their psycho-emotional well-being in times of pandemic. The virtual services of the Respectful Upbringing multiplatform were an alternative to orient 5,085 people and their families. Additionally, the Counseling Service of the a+ Adolescent Spaces Center supported 14,811 adolescents and their family members with psychological, self-care and mental health tools. Also, 1,882 children were benefitted with playing resources delivered to pediatric wards, to contribute to their psycho-emotional well-being during admission due to COVID-19. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/01/2022
